{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"37a5c165-5de1-471a-bc35-d034ae70bc0f","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing a .dmp file, but note that none of my available skills cover **dump analysis** (only dump collection and symbolication of specific crash log formats).\n\nHere's how you can analyze it:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (recommended for managed .NET):\n```bash\ndotnet-dump analyze <path-to-your.dmp>\n```\n\nOnce inside, useful commands:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all managed threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n**Using `lldb` (Linux) or WinDbg (Windows):**\n- Load SOS: `dotnet sos install`, then in lldb: `plugin load libsosplugin.so`\n- Same SOS commands: `clrstack`, `pe`, `dumpheap`, etc.\n\n---\n\n**Want me to try analyzing it here?** If so:\n1. Tell me the path to the `.dmp` file\n2. I'll check if `dotnet-dump` is available and walk through the analysis\n\nOtherwise, start with `dotnet-dump analyze your.dmp` then run `pe` to see the exception that caused the crash.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e503875b-6384-4a98-a6fb-e4cc1c1d9440","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me look at the available skills to see if any of them are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstones, not .dmp files\n\n\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing dump files. Since I can't use the available tools for this task, I should guide the user through analyzing the dump themselves using `dotnet-dump analyze` or check if they've uploaded the file so I can help them interpret the results.","outputTokens":603,"requestId":"501F:B7F6F:293F78:337326:69F55588"},"id":"6f456d0c-c8a4-490e-9803-7fe223053010","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:38:31.943Z","parentId":"d84d6c09-76e5-4c50-84ba-0d18c7e80abc"}
